==C==

{{glossary}}
{{term|term= C, C−, C+}}
{{defn|defn= In [[lichenology]], "C" is an abbreviation for the test result of placing 5% solution of [[calcium hypochlorite]] or [[sodium hypochlorite]] (e.g. household bleach without additives) on the [[#cortex|cortex]] or the [[#medulla|medulla]] of a [[lichen]], to note the change in color, with no reaction noted as "C−", and production of a bright colour noted as "C+".}}

{{term|term= caducous |content= [[caducous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Falling off early; for example, the [[#sepal|sepals]] of poppies, which fall off when the petals begin to open. Compare [[#persistent|persistent]] and [[#fugacious|fugacious]].}}

[[File:Dianthus chinensis - Raspberry parfait 3.jpg|thumb|right|''[[Dianthus chinensis]]'' has a '''caespitose''' growth habit]]
{{term|term= caespitose}}
{{defn|defn= Tufted, e.g. the growth form of some grasses.}}

{{term|term= [[calcareous]]|content= [[calcareous]]}}
{{defn|defn= A [[soil type]] that is rich in [[calcium carbonate]]; a lichen substrate rock type that is largely composed of calcium carbonate.}}

{{term|term= [[callose]]|content= [[callose]]}}
{{defn|defn= Hardened, thickened, callous.}}

[[File:Callus1.jpg|thumb|right|Callus tissue of tobacco, ''[[Nicotiana tabacum]]'', growing on a nutrient medium in [[plant tissue culture]]]] 
{{term|term= callus}}
{{defn|no=1|defn= {{ghat|''pl.'' calli}} A protruding mass of tissue.}} 
{{defn|no=2|defn= Undifferentiated tissue growth formed in response to wounding; may be grown ''in vitro''.}}  
{{defn|no=3|defn= In orchids, fleshy outgrowths from the labellum which can be variously shaped from papillae to plates.}} 
{{defn|no=4|defn= In grasses, a hardened extension from the base of a floret (formed from the rachilla joint and/or the base of the lemma) which may or may not elongate and is often covered in hairs or bristles.}}

{{term|term= calyciflorous}}
{{defn|defn= Having petals and stamens attached to the [[#calyx|calyx]].}}

{{term|term= calycophyll |content= [[calycophyll]] }}
{{defn|defn= A leaf-like structure formed from a sepal or calyx lobe which enlarges, usually many-fold, before or after [[#anthesis|anthesis]], especially when most of the sepals or calyx lobes retain their original size. More extreme than an accrescent calyx, calycophylls are found in [[Rubiaceae]]. cf. [[#semaphyll|semaphyll]], [[#pterophyll|pterophyll]].}}

{{term|term= calyculate}}
{{defn|defn= Having an [[#epicalyx|epicalyx]].}}

{{term|term= calyculus |content= calyculus}}
{{defn|no=1|defn= A cup-shaped structure formed from [[#bract|bracts]].}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= In some [[Asteraceae]], a circle of bracts below the [[#involucre|involucre]].}}

{{term|term= calyptra |content= [[calyptra]] }}
{{defn|defn= A hood or lid. See [[#operculum|operculum]].}}

{{term|term= calyx |content= [[Sepal|calyx]] }}
{{defn|defn= 
{{ghat|''pl.'' calyces}} A collective term for the [[#sepal|sepals]] of one flower; the outer whorl of a flower, usually green. Compare [[#corolla|corolla]].}}

{{term|term= calyx tube |content= [[calyx tube]] }}
{{defn|defn= A tube formed by the fusion of the sepals ([[#calyx|calyx]]), at least at the base.}}

{{term|term= cambium |content= [[cambium]] }}
{{defn|defn= A tissue layer that provides partially undifferentiated cells for plant growth.}}
