{{term|term= Casparian strip |content= [[Casparian strip]] }}
{{defn|defn= A continuous band of [[suberin]] in the radial primary cell walls of the [[#endodermis|endodermis]] in vascular plant stems and roots that forms a permeability barrier to the passive diffusion of external water and solutes into the vascular tissue. }}

{{term|term= casual alien |content= [[casual alien]] }}
{{defn|defn= A plant that appears with no apparent human assistance but does not develop a sustained population(s). Plants that persist only by new introductions. Compare [[#alien|alien]].}}

{{term|term= cataphyll |content= [[cataphyll]] }}
{{defn|defn= Early leaf forms of plants or shoots, such as cotyledons, bud-scales, rhizome-scales; anatomically they are leaves, but do not develop to perform the usual functions of photosynthetic leaves.}}

{{term|term= catkin |content= [[catkin]] }}
{{defn|defn= A spike, usually pendulous, in which the mostly small flowers are [[#unisexual|unisexual]] and without a conspicuous [[#perianth|perianth]], e.g. [[Salix|willows]], [[Populus|poplars]], [[Quercus|oaks]] and [[casuarina]]s.  The individual flowers often have scaly [[#bract|bracts]]; they are generally wind-pollinated. The [[#catkin|catkins]] are usually shed as a unit.}}

{{term|term= caudate }}
