{{defn|defn= Of flowers that are pollinated when the [[#perianth|perianth]] is open. Compare [[#cleistogamous|cleistogamous]].}}

{{term|term= chasmophyte |content= [[chasmophyte]] }}
{{defn|defn= A plant adapted to growing in crevices or hollows, such as in cliff faces. Compare [[#cremnophyte|cremnophyte]].<ref name= "BotGloss">Jackson, Benjamin, Daydon; A Glossary of Botanic Terms with their Derivation and Accent; Published by Gerald Duckworth & Co. London, 4th ed 1928</ref><ref name= "Jaeger">{{cite book |author=Jaeger, Edmund Carroll |title=A source-book of biological names and terms |publisher=Thomas |location=Springfield, Ill |year=1959 |pages= |isbn=978-0-398-06179-1 |oclc= |doi= }}</ref>}}

{{term|term= chimera |content= [[chimera (plant)|chimera]] }}
{{defn|defn= An individual composed of two or more genetically different tissues, most commonly as a result of a graft and sometimes within the individual, by mutations and irregularities that occur during cell division.}}

{{term|term= chiropterophilous |content= [[chiropterophilous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Pollinated by [[bat]]s.}}

{{term|term= chlorophyll |content= [[chlorophyll]] }}
{{defn|defn= A green pigment in chloroplasts essential for [[#photosynthesis|photosynthesis]].}}

{{term|term= chloroplast |content= [[chloroplast]] }}
{{defn|defn= An organelle present in plant cells which contains [[#chlorophyll|chlorophyll]].}}

{{term|term= chlorosis |content= [[chlorosis]] }}
{{defn|defn= An abnormal lack or paleness of color in a normally green organ.}}

{{term|term= cilia |content= cilia {{anchor|cilia}} }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''sing.'' ''cilium''; ''adj.'' '''[[#ciliate|ciliate]]'''}} Very small hairs or hair-like protrusions more or less confined to the [[#margin|margins]] of an organ, as with eyelashes; in motile cells, minute, hair-like protrusions which aid motility.}}

{{term|term= circinate }}
{{defn|defn= Spirally coiled with the tip innermost, e.g. circinate [[#vernation|vernation]] of the developing fronds of most ferns.}}

{{term|term= cladode |content= [[cladode]] }}
{{defn|defn= A [[#photosynthesis|photosynthetic]] stem, often leaf-like and usually with foliage leaves either absent or much reduced. Compare [[#phyllode|phyllode]].}}

{{term|term= class |content= [[class (biology)|class]] }}
{{defn|defn= The principal category for taxa ranking between [[#division|division]] and [[#order|order]].}}

{{term|term= clathrate }}
{{defn|defn= Shaped like a net or lattice; pierced with apertures, as with a cage.}}

{{term|term= clavate |content= [[clavate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Club-shaped.}}

{{term|term= claw }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= A narrow, stalk-like, [[#basal|basal]] portion of a [[#petal|petal]], [[#sepal|sepal]] or [[#bract|bract]].}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= In ''[[Melaleuca]]'', the united portion of a [[#stamen|stamen]] bundle.}}

{{term|term= cleistogamous |content= [[cleistogamous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having flowers which self-pollinate and never open fully or self-pollinate before opening. Compare [[#chasmogamous|chasmogamous]].}}

{{term|term= climber |content= [[Vine|climber]] }}
{{defn|defn= A plant growing more or less erect by leaning on or twining around another structure for support, or by clinging with [[#tendril|tendrils]].}}

{{term|term= cline |content= [[cline (biology)|cline]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''adj.'' '''clinal'''}} A continuous morphological variation in form within a species or sometimes between two species.}}

{{term|term= clone |content= [[cloning|clone]] }}
{{defn|defn= A plant derived from the vegetative reproduction of a parent plant, with both plants having identical genetic constitutions.}}

{{term|term= coalescent |content= [[coalescent]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having plant parts fused or grown together to form a single unit.}}

{{term|term= cochleariform |content= [[:wikt: cochleariform|cochleariform]] }}
{{defn|defn= Concave and spoon-shaped.}}

{{term|term= cochleate |content= [[:wikt: cochleate|cochleate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Coiled like a snail's shell.}}

{{term|term= coenobium |content= [[Coenobium (morphology)|coenobium]] }}
{{defn|defn= An arranged colony of [[algae]] that acts like a single organism.}}

{{term|term= coenocyte |content= [[coenocyte]] }}
{{defn|defn= A single cell with multiple [[Cell nucleus|nuclei]], formed when nuclear division was not followed by [[cytokinesis]].}}

{{term|term= collenchyma |content= [[Ground tissue#collenchyma|collenchyma]] }}
{{defn|defn= A specialized tissue consisting of living cells with unevenly thickened [[cellulose]] and [[pectin]] [[cell walls]] that performs a support function in organs such as leaves and young stems that are composed of primary plant tissues.}}

{{term|term= colleter |content= [[Colleter (botany)|colleter]] }}
{{defn|defn= A multicellular, glandular hair that usually produces a mucilaginous substance and is located on sepals, stipules, or petioles, or on nearby parts of stems; commonly found on plants in the order Gentianales.}}

{{term|term= columella |content= [[columella]] }}
{{defn|defn= In flowering plants, the central axis of the cone or fruit, e.g. in ''[[Callitris]]''.}}

{{term|term= column |content= [[column (botany)|column]] }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= A structure extending above ovary and incorporating the style and stamens; [[#gynostemium|gynostemium]], e.g. in orchids.}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= In grasses, the lower, stouter, and usually twisted part of an [[#awn|awn]], distinct from the slender upper part or bristle.}}

{{term|term= columnar |content= [[columnar]] }}
{{defn|defn= Shaped like a column.}}

{{term|term= commercial name |content= [[commercial name]] }}
{{defn|defn= A name often of no botanical standing and not governed by the [[ICNCP]]. The term generally applies to names such as Trademark Names, names covered by Plant Breeders Rights, Patents and Promotional Names, which are often used to enhance the sale of a plant.}}

{{term|term= commissure |content= [[commissure]] }}
{{defn|defn= The seam or face at which two carpels adhere.}}

{{term|term= community |content= [[Plant community|community]] }}
{{defn|defn= An ecological assemblage of plants that characteristically occur together.}}

{{term|term= compound }}
{{defn|defn= Composed of several parts, e.g. a leaf with [[#leaflets|leaflets]], a [[#gynoecium|gynoecium]] with several [[#carpel|carpels]], or an inflorescence made up of smaller inflorescences.}}

[[File:Aesculus californica-12.jpg|thumb|right|upright=0.7|California buckeye (''[[Aesculus californica]]'') has a '''compound palmate''' leaf because the leaflets radiate out from a central point]]
{{term|term= [[compound palmate]]}}
{{defn|defn= Having [[#leaflets|leaflets]] that radiate from a central point (usually at the top of a [[#petiole|petiole]]) like spread-out fingers radiating from the palm of a hand.}}

{{term|term= compressed |content= [[Compression (botany)|compressed]] }}
{{defn|defn= Flattened lengthwise, either laterally (from side to side) or dorsally (from front to back).}}

{{term|term= concolorous |content= [[concolorous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having the same colour throughout; uniformly coloured.}}

[[File:Nicotiana × sanderae flowers.jpg|thumb|right|The lobes of the [[#corolla|corolla]] of ''[[Nicotiana]]'' flowers are [[#conduplicate|conduplicate]] in the bud]]
{{term|term= conduplicate |content= [[conduplicate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Arranged such that two sides of a flat surface are folded along the midline to face each other. See also [[wikt:ptyxis|ptyxis]], [[aestivation (botany)|aestivation]], and [[vernation]].}}

{{term|term= cone |content= [[cone (botany)|cone]] }}
{{defn|defn= A fruit, usually woody, [[#ovoid|ovoid]] to [[#globular|globular]], including [[#scale|scales]], [[#bract|bracts]] or [[#bracteoles|bracteoles]] arranged around a central axis, e.g. in [[gymnosperms]], especially [[conifers]] and ''[[Casuarina]]''.}}

{{term|term= conflorescence}}
{{defn|defn= A rarely used term describing substantial differences between the overall structure of an [[#inflorescence|inflorescence]] and that of its individual branches, e.g. the bottlebrush multiple-flower head of members of the genus ''[[Callistemon]]''.}}

{{term|term= connate |content= [[connation|connate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Fused to another organ (or organs) of the same kind, e.g. petals in a [[#corolla|corolla]] tube. Compare [[#adnate|adnate]].}}

{{term|term= connective |content= connective }}
{{defn|defn= The part of an [[#anther|anther]] that connects the anther cells.}}

{{term|term= connivent |content= [[connivent]] }}
{{defn|defn= Coming into contact or converging.}}

{{term|term= conspecific |content= [[conspecific]] }}
{{defn|defn= Belonging to the same species.}}

{{term|term= contiguous |content= [[Geographic contiguity|contiguous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Adjoining, touching, but not united.}}

{{term|term= contort |content= [[contort (botany)|contort]] }}
{{defn|defn= (of sepals and petals) A type of imbricate [[aestivation]] in which one side of each segment overlaps one of the adjacent segments and the other side is overlapped by the other adjacent segment. See [[#convolute|convolute]].}}

{{term|term= contorted |content= contorted }}
{{defn|defn= Twisted out of the normal shape.}}

{{term|term= convolute |content= [[convolute (botany)|convolute]] }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= Referring to the arrangement of floral or foliar organs in a bud when each organ or segment has one edge overlapping the adjacent organ or segment; a form of [[#imbricate|imbricate]] arrangement; [[#contort|contort]].}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= (of leaves) A type of [[vernation]] in which one leaf is rolled up inside another.}}
{{defn|no=3|defn= A type of vernation of two leaves at a node, in which one half of each leaf is exposed and the other half is wrapped inside the other leaf.}}

{{term|term= cordate |content= [[cordate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Heart-shaped, with the notch lowermost; of the base of a leaf, like the notched part of a heart.}}

{{term|term= coriaceous |content= coriaceous }}
{{defn|defn= Leathery; stiff and tough, but somewhat flexible.}}

{{term|term= corm |content= [[corm]] }}
{{defn|defn= A fleshy, swollen stem base, usually underground and functioning in the storage of food reserves, with buds naked or covered by very thin scales; a type of [[#rootstock|rootstock]]. Adjectives derived from "corm" include "cormose" and "cormous".}}

{{term|term= corolla |content= [[corolla (flower)|corolla]] }}
{{defn|defn= A collective term for the [[#petal|petals]] of a flower. Compare [[#calyx|calyx]].}}

[[File:Passiflora kermesina3.jpg|thumb|right|The '''corona''' of this ''[[Passiflora]]'' flower is a ring of purple filaments between the petals and the stamens]]
{{term|term= corona |content= [[Corona (perianth)|corona]]}}
{{defn|no=1|defn= In flowering plants, a ring of structures that may be united in a tube, arising from the [[#corolla|corolla]] or [[#perianth|perianth]] of a flower and standing between the perianth lobes and the [[#stamen|stamens]]. The trumpet of a [[daffodil]] is a corona.}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= In grasses, a hardened ring of tissue surmounting the [[#lemma|lemma]] in some species.}}

{{term|term= cortex |content= [[Cortex (botany)|cortex]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''pl.'' cortexes, cortices}} In lichens, the "skin" or outer layer of [[#thallus|thallus]] tissue that covers the [[#medulla|medulla]]. [[#Fruticose|Fruticose]] lichens have one cortex encircling the branches, even flattened, leaf-like forms; [[#foliose|foliose]] lichens have different upper and lower cortices; [[#crustose|crustose]], [[#placodioid|placodioid]] and [[#squamulose|squamulose]] lichens have an upper cortex but no lower cortex; and [[#leprose|leprose]] lichens lack any cortex.}}

{{term|term= corticolous |content= [[corticolous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Growing on bark or on wood with the bark stripped off. Compare [[#lignicolous|lignicolous]].}}

{{term|term= corymb |content= [[corymb]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''adj.'' '''corymbose'''}} An inflorescence with branches arising at different points but reaching about the same height, giving the flower cluster a flat-topped appearance.}}

{{term|term= costa |content= costa {{anchor|Costa}} }}
{{defn|defn= A [[rib]].}}

{{term|term= costapalmate }}
{{defn|defn= Having a definite costa (midrib), unlike the typical [[#palmate|palmate]] or fan leaf, but with the leaflets arranged radially as in a palmate leaf.}}

{{term|term= cotyledon |content= [[cotyledon]] }}
{{defn|defn= The primary leaf or leaves of a plant embryo which upon germination develops into the seed-leaf or the first set of leaves.}}

{{term|term= craspedodromous |content= [[craspedodromous]] }}
{{defn|defn= [[#pinnate|Pinnate]] [[Parallel venation|venation]] in which the [[#secondary vein|secondary veins]] terminate at the [[#margin|margins]], often as teeth.}}

{{term|term= crateriform |content= [[crateriform]] }}
{{defn|defn= In the shape of a saucer or shallow cup; hemispherical or more shallow .}}  

{{term|term= cremnophyte |content= [[cremnophyte]] }}
{{defn|defn= A plant adapted to growing on, especially hanging from, cliff faces or crevices. Compare [[Glossary of botanical terms#chasmophyte|chasmophyte]].<ref name= "BotGloss">Jackson, Benjamin, Daydon; A Glossary of Botanic Terms with their Derivation and Accent; Published by Gerald Duckworth & Co. London, 4th ed 1928</ref><ref name= "Jaeger">{{cite book |author=Jaeger, Edmund Carroll |title=A source-book of biological names and terms |publisher=Thomas |location=Springfield, Ill |year=1959 |pages= |isbn=978-0-398-06179-1 |oclc= |doi= }}</ref> }}  

{{term|term= crenate |content= [[crenate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having blunt or rounded teeth; [[scallop]]ed.}}

{{term|term= crenulate |content= [[crenulate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Minutely scalloped.}}

{{term|term= crisped |content= [[:wikt:crisped|crisped]] }}
{{defn|defn= Finely curled, as with the edges of leaves and petals.}}

{{term|term= cristarque cell |content= [[cristarque cell]] }}
{{defn|defn= A [[sclereid]] which contains a [[Druse (botany)|druse]] and has the [[lignin]] deposited excentrically on the [[cell wall]] to form a cup shape, or in [[cross section (geometry)|cross section]], a ∪-shape.}}

{{term|term= crown |content= [[Crown (botany)|crown]] }}
{{defn|defn= See [[#canopy|canopy]].}}

{{term|term= cross |content= [[Hybrid (biology)|cross]] }}
{{defn|defn= To make something interbreed; the act of hybridization.}}

{{term|term= cruciform |content= [[cruciform]] }}
{{defn|defn= Cross-shaped.}}

{{term|term= crustaceous |content= [[crustaceous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Hard, thin and brittle.}}

[[File:N2 Lichen.jpg|thumb|right|upright=0.55|[[Crustose]] [[lichen]]s on a wall]]
{{term|term= crustose }}
{{defn|defn= Forming a closely applied surface layer or crust.}}

{{term|term= cryptogams |content= [[cryptogams]] }}
{{defn|defn= A collective term for the "lower plants" which produce spores and do not have stamens, ovaries or seeds; literally plants whose sexual reproductive organs are not conspicuous. Typically includes the ferns, bryophytes and algae, and sometimes fungi (including lichenized fungi). Compare [[#phanerogam|phanerogam]].}}

{{term|term= cucullate |content= [[Cucullate (plant)|cucullate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Hood-like or hooded, commonly referring to the shape of leaves or petals, e.g. ''[[Pelargonium cucullatum]]''. Similarly derived terms include ''cuculliform'' and ''cuccularis''.}}

{{term|term= culm |content= [[culm (botany)|culm]] }}
{{defn|defn= In grasses, sedges, rushes, and some other monocotyledons, an aerial stem bearing the inflorescence; strictly, from the base of the plant to the lowest [[#involucral bract|involucral bract]] (or base of the inflorescence).}}

{{term|term= cultigen |content= [[cultigen]] }}
{{defn|defn= A plant whose origin or selection is primarily due to intentional human activity.}}

{{term|term= cultivar |content= [[cultivar]] }}
{{defn|defn= A term derived from "cultivated variety" denoting an assemblage of cultivated plants clearly distinguished by one or more characters (morphological, physiological, cytological, chemical or other); when reproduced (sexually or asexually), the assemblage retains its distinguishing characters. A cultivar may arise in cultivation or be introduced from the wild. It is a variant that is of horticultural interest or value. Cultivar names are written with single quotation marks around them e.g. 'Blue Carpet' or 'Alba'. All new names established after 1 January 1959 must be in common language (that is, not in Latin) but names established in Latin prior to this date are retained in Latin form.}}

{{term|term= cultivar epithet |content= [[cultivar epithet]] }}
{{defn|defn= The defining part of a name that denominates a cultivar.  Cultivars are designated by fancy (q.v.) epithets appended either to the scientific name or to the common name of the taxon to which they belong; they are not italicized but placed in single quotation marks, for example ''Rubus nitidoides'' 'Merton Early'. 'Merton Early' is the cultivar epithet.}}

{{term|term= cuneate }}
{{defn|defn= Wedge-shaped, with straight sides converging at base.}}

{{term|term= cupule |content= [[calybium and cupule|cupule]] }}
{{defn|defn= A cup-shaped structure composed of coalescent [[#bract|bracts]], such as the cup of an [[acorn]]. See [[#calybium|calybium]].}}

{{term|term= cupular |content= [[cupular]] }}
{{defn|defn= Shaped like a [[#cupule|cupule]].}}

{{term|term= cupulate |content= [[cupulate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Bearing [[#cupule|cupules]].}}

{{term|term= cupuliform |content= [[cupuliform]] }}
{{defn|defn= Nearly hemispherical, shaped like a cupola or dome.}}

{{term|term= cusp |content= [[:wikt:cusp|cusp]] }}
{{defn|defn= A pointed tip, hence [[#cuspidate|cuspidate]].}}

{{term|term= cuspidate |content= [[:wikt:cuspidate|cuspidate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Tipped with a [[#cusp|cusp]], as with some leaves.}}

{{term|term= cuticle |content= [[Plant cuticle|cuticle]] }}
{{defn|defn= A waterproofing layer covering the [[#epidermis|epidermis]] of aerial plant surfaces and composed of the polymers [[cutin]], and/or [[Cutan (polymer)|cutan]] and waxes.}}

{{term|term= cutting |content= [[cutting (plant)|cutting]] }}
{{defn|defn= An [[#apical|apical]] tip of shoot structure, root or leaf which is cut from a plant and used for vegetative propagation.}}

{{term|term= cyathium |content= [[cyathium]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''pl.'' cyathia}} An inflorescence of [[#unisexual|unisexual]] flowers surrounded by [[#involucre|involucral bracts]], especially the flowers of ''[[Euphorbia]]''.}}

[[File:Euphorbia Milii flowers.jpg|thumb|right|upright=0.55|''[[Euphorbia milii]]'' is commercially grown for the aesthetic appearance of its brightly colored, [[bract]]-like structures called '''[[#cyathophylls|cyathophylls]]''', which sit below the [[inflorescence]]]]
{{term|term= cyathophyll |content= cyathophyll }}
{{defn|defn= The [[bract]]-like structure of a ''[[Euphorbia]]'' on which the involucre sits, usually but not always occurring in twos. They may sometimes be brightly colored and confused with [[petals]].}}

{{term|term= cylindrical |content= cylindrical }}
{{defn|defn= Rod-like and two to three times as long as wide. Compare [[#baculiform|baculiform]].}}

{{term|term=cynaroid |content=[[cynaroid]]}}
{{defn|defn= See [[#carduoid|carduoid]]}}

{{term|term= cyme |content= [[Cyme (botany)|cyme]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''adj.'' '''cymose'''}} A type of [[#inflorescence|inflorescence]] in which the main axis and all lateral branches end in a flower (each lateral may be repeatedly branched).}}

{{term|term= cypsela |content= [[Asteraceae#Fruits and seeds|cypsela]] }}
{{defn|defn= A dry, one-seeded, [[#indehiscent|indehiscent]] fruit formed from an inferior ovary.}}

