==G==
{{glossary}}

{{term|term= galbulus |content= [[galbulus]] }}
{{defn|defn= (in [[gymnosperms]]) A fleshy cone ([[#megastrobilus|megastrobilus]]); chiefly relates to those borne by [[Juniperus|junipers]] and [[Cupressus|cypresses]] and often mistakenly called [[berry (botany)|berries]].}}

{{term|term= gamete |content= [[gamete]] }}
{{defn|defn= A cell or nucleus that fuses with another of the opposite sex during sexual reproduction.}}

{{term|term= gametophyte |content= [[gametophyte]] }}
{{defn|defn= The [[ploidy#haploid and monoploid|haploid]] multicellular phase in the [[alternation of generations]] of plants and algae that bears [[#gametes|gametes]]. In [[bryophytes]] the gametophyte is the dominant vegetative phase; in ferns and their allies it is a small free-living plant known as the prothallus; in gymnosperms and angiosperms the gametophytes are reduced to microscopic structures dependent on the [[#sporophyte|sporophyte]], male gametophytes contained in [[pollen]] grains and females contained within the [[ovule]]s. }}

{{term|term= gene pool |content= [[gene pool]] }}
{{defn|defn= The complete range of genetic variation found within a population.}}

{{term|term= genus |content= [[genus]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''pl.'' genera}} A group of one or more {{#species|species}} with features or ancestry (or both) in common. Genus is the principal category of taxa intermediate in rank between [[#family|family]] and species in the standard nomenclatural hierarchy.}}

{{term|term= generic name |content= [[name of a biological genus|generic name]] }}
{{defn|defn= The name of a taxonomic [[#genus|genus]], such as ''[[Acacia]]'' and ''[[Eucalyptus]]''.}}

