{{defn|defn= growth habit in which several woody stems arise separately from a [[#lignotuber|lignotuber]]; a plant with such a growth habit, e.g. many [[Eucalyptus]] species; vegetation characterized by such plants. }}

{{term|term= mangrove |content= [[mangrove]] }}
{{defn|defn= a shrub or small tree growing in salt or brackish water, usually characterized by [[pneumatophore]]s. Tropical coastal vegetation characterized by such species. }}

{{term|term= margin |content= [[Leaf margin|margin]] }}
{{defn|defn= the edge, as in the edge of a leaf blade.}}

{{term|term= marginal }}
{{defn|defn= occurring at or very close to the [[#margin|margin]].}}

{{term|term= marsh |content= [[marsh]] }}
{{defn|defn= a waterlogged area; swamp.}}

{{term|term= mast |content= [[Mast (botany)|mast]] }}
{{defn|defn= edible fruit and nuts produced by woody species of plants, i.e. [[acorn]]s and [[beech]]mast, that wildlife species and some domestic animals consume.}}

{{term|term= mealy }}
{{defn|defn= covered with coarse, floury powder.}}

{{term|term= medulla }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= In a [[lichen]], the typically undifferentiated tissue underneath the cortex of the [[thallus]], or between the upper and lower [[#cortex|cortex]] if both are present. The [[medulla (lichenology)|medulla]] is analogous to the tissues underneath the [[Epidermis (botany)|epidermis]] (skin) of a leaf. The uppermost region commonly contains most of the [[photobiont]]s.}}
{{defn|no=2|defn=[[#pith|pith]]. See also [[medullary ray (botany)|medullary rays]] in wood.}}

{{term|term= megasporangium }}
{{defn|defn= the larger of two kinds of sporangium produced by [[heterospory|heterosporous]] plants, producing large spores that contain the female [[#gametophyte|gametophyte]]s. Compare [[#microsporangium|microsporangium]].}}

{{term|term= megaspore |content= [[megaspore]] }}
{{defn|defn= the larger of two kinds of spores produced by a [[heterospory|heterosporous]] plant, giving rise to the female [[#gametophyte|gametophyte]]. Compare [[#microspore|microspore]].}}

{{term|term= megasporophyll }}
{{defn|defn= in [[heterospory|hetersoporous]] plants, a modified leaf bearing one or more [[#megasporangium|megasporangia]]. Compare [[#microsporophyll|microsporophyll]].}}

{{term|term= megastrobilus |content= [[megastrobilus]] }}
{{defn|defn= the larger of two kinds of cones or [[#strobilus|strobili]] produced by [[gymnosperms]], being female and producing the seeds. Compare [[#microstrobilus|microstrobilus]].}}

{{term|term= membranous |content= [[Biological membrane|membranous]] }}
{{defn|defn= thin, translucent and flexible, seldom green.}}

{{term|term= mericarp |content= [[mericarp]] }}
{{defn|defn= one segment of a fruit (a [[#schizocarp|schizocarp]]) that splits at maturity into units derived from the individual [[#carpel|carpels]], or a carpel, usually 1-seeded, released by the break-up at maturity of a fruit formed from 2 or more joined carpels.}}

{{term|term= meristem |content= [[meristem]] }}
{{defn|defn= an actively dividing tissue.}}

{{term|term= mesic |content= [[mesic habitat|mesic]] }}
{{defn|defn= moist, avoiding both extremes of drought and wet; pertaining to conditions of moderate moisture or water supply; applied to organisms (vegetation) occupying moist habitats.}}

{{term|term= mesocarp |content= [[mesocarp]] }}
{{defn|defn= The fleshy portion of the wall of a [[#succulent|succulent]] fruit inside the skin and outside the stony layer (if any), surrounding the seed(s); [[#sarcocarp|sarcocarp]].}}

{{term|term= mesomorphic |content= mesomorphic }}
{{defn|defn= Soft and with little fibrous tissue, but not [[#succulent|succulent]].}}

{{term|term= mesophyll |content= mesophyll }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= [[Mesophyll tissue]], photosynthetic tissue of a leaf, the central tissues between the upper and lower epidermis.}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= In ecology, the blade of a [[leaf]] or leaflet that has a surface area 4500–18225 mm<sup>2</sup>; A plant, or vegetation, that has mesophyll (sized) leaves.}}

{{term|term= mesophyllous |content= [[mesophyllous]] }}
{{defn|defn= (of vegetation) Of moist habitats and having mostly large and soft leaves.}}

{{term|term= mesophyte |content= [[mesophyte]] }}
