{{term|term= monoecious |content= [[monoecious]] }}
{{defn|defn= Of vascular plants, [[#hermaphrodite|hermaphroditic]], with all flowers [[#bisexual|bisexual]]; or with male and female reproductive structures in separate flowers but on the same plant; or of an inflorescence that has unisexual flowers of both sexes. Compare [[#dioecious|dioecious]].}}

{{term|term= monoicous |content= [[monoicous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Of bryophyte gametophytes, [[#hermaphrodite|hermaphroditic]], [[#bisexual|bisexual]], when both male and female reproductive structures develop on the same individual. Compare [[#dioicous|dioicous]].}}

{{term|term= monograph |content= [[monograph]] }}
{{defn|defn= of a group of plants, a comprehensive treatise presenting an analysis and synthesis of taxonomic knowledge of that taxon; the fullest account possible (at the time) of a family, tribe or genus.  It is generally worldwide in scope and evaluates all taxonomic treatments of that taxon including studies of its evolutionary relationships with other related taxa, and cytological, genetic, morphological, palaeobotanical and ecological studies.  The term is often incorrectly applied to any systematic work devoted to a single taxon. Compare [[#revision|revision]].}}

{{term|term= monomorphic |content= [[Polymorphism (biology)|monomorphic]] }}
{{defn|defn= of one type, rather than several. See also [[#dimorphic|dimorphic]] (two types) and [[Polymorphism (biology)|polymorphic]] (many types)}}

{{term|term= monophyllous |content= [[:wikt:monophyllous|monophyllous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having a single leaf.}}

{{term|term= monopodial }}
{{defn|defn= a mode of stem growth and branching in which the main axis is formed by a single dominant meristem. }}

{{term|term= monostromatic |content= [[monostromatic]] }}
{{defn|defn= Being a single cell thick, as in the [[alga]] ''[[Monostroma]]''.}}

{{term|term= monotypic |content= [[monotypic]] }}
{{defn|defn= containing only one taxon of the next lower rank, e.g. a family with only one genus, or a genus that includes only a single species.}}

{{term|term= morphology |content= [[Polymorphism (biology)|morphology]]}}
{{defn|defn=  the shape or form of an organism or part thereof.}}

{{term|term= mucro |content= [[Leaf|mucro]] }}
{{defn|defn= Diminutive: mucronule. A sharp, short point, generally at the tip of a leaf or the tip of the midrib of a compound leaf.<ref name="BotGloss">Jackson, Benjamin, Daydon; A Glossary of Botanic Terms with their Derivation and Accent; Published by Gerald Duckworth & Co. London, 4th ed 1928</ref>}}

{{term|term= mucronate |content= [[Leaf|mucronate]] }}
{{defn|defn= terminating in a mucro.}}

{{term|term= multiple fruit |content= [[multiple fruit]] }}
