{{term|term= perigonium}}
{{defn|defn= in [[flowering plants]] see [[perianth]]}}
{{defn|no=2|defn=  in [[moss]]es, the leaves surrounding the antheridia, also called a [[#splash cup|spash-cup]], e.g. in ''[[Polytrichum juniperinum]]''. }}

{{term|term= perigynium}}
{{defn|defn= a sac from a modified tubular bract, or when fully closed an [[#utricle|utricle]], around the [[#pistillate flower|pistillate flower]] of [[sedge]]s}}

{{term|term= perigynous |content= [[perigynous]] }}
{{defn|defn= borne around the ovary, i.e. of perianth segments and stamens arising from a cup-like or tubular extension of receptacle (free from the ovary but extending above its base). Compare [[#epigynous|epigynous]], [[#hypogynous|hypogynous]].}}

{{term|term= persistent }}
{{defn|defn= remaining attached to the plant beyond the usual time of falling, for instance sepals not falling after flowering, flower parts remaining through maturity of fruit. Compare [[#deciduous|deciduous]], [[#caducous|caducous]].}}

{{term|term= perule |content= [[perule]] }}
{{ghat|(''adj.'' ''perulate'')}}
{{defn|no=1|defn= the scales covering a [[leaf]] or [[flower bud]], or a reduced scale like leaf surrounding the bud. Buds lacking perulae are referred to as 'naked'}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= in Camellias the final [[#bract|bracts]] and sepals become indistinguishable and are called perules.}}
{{defn|no=3|defn= a kind of sac formed by the adherent bases of the two lateral sepals in certain orchids.}}

{{term|term= petal |content= [[petal]] }}
{{defn|defn= in a flower, one of the segments or divisions of the inner whorl of non-fertile parts surrounding the fertile organs, usually soft and conspicuously coloured. Compare [[#sepal|sepal]].}}

{{term|term= petaloid |content= [[petaloid]] }}
{{defn|defn= like a [[#petal|petal]]; soft in texture and coloured conspicuously.}}

{{term|term= petiolate }}
{{defn|defn= a leaf with a petiole. Compare [[#sessile|sessile]]. }}

{{term|term= petiole |content= [[Petiole (botany)|petiole]] }}
{{defn|defn= the stalk of a leaf.}}

{{term|term= petiolule |content= [[petiolule]] }}
{{defn|defn= the stalk of a leaflet.}}

{{term|term= petricolous |content= [[petricolous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Rock-dwelling; living on or among rocks.}}

{{term|term= phaneranthous |content= [[phaneranthous]] }}
{{defn|defn= showy, as in showy flowers that advertise to [[pollinators]], as opposed to [[#aphananthous|aphananthous]] (unshowy)}}

{{term|term= phanerogam |content= [[phanerogam]] }}
{{defn|defn= gymnosperms and angiosperms; plants producing stamens and gynoecia; literally plants with conspicuous sexual reproductive organs. Compare [[cryptogam]]s.}}

{{term|term= phenology |content= [[phenology]] }}
{{defn|defn= the study of the timing of seasonal biological phenomena, such as flowering, leaf emergence, fruit ripening and leaf fall. }}

{{term|term= phloem |content= [[phloem]] }}
{{defn|defn= a specialised conducting tissue in [[vascular plants]] that transports [[sucrose]] from the leaves to other plant organs. }}

{{term|term= photobiont |content= [[photobiont]] }}
{{defn|defn= In a lichen, the component that does the [[photosynthesis]], the green algae ([[Chlorophyta]]) or blue-green algae ([[Cyanobacteria]]). (compare to [[#mycobiont|mycobiont]], the [[fungal]] component.) Also called the '''[[#phycobiont|phycobiont]]'''.}}

{{term|term= photosynthesis |content= [[photosynthesis]] }}
{{defn|defn= The process by which energy from sunlight is used to convert [[carbon dioxide]] and [[water]] into [[simple sugar]]s in cells containing [[#chloroplast|chloroplasts]]. All plants, except certain [[#parasite|parasites]], can perform photosynthesis.}}

{{term|term= phycobiont |content= [[phycobiont]] }}
{{defn|defn= In a lichen, a synonym for [[#photobiont|photobiont]]}}

{{term|term= phyllid |content= phyllid }}
{{defn|defn= A leaf-like extension of the stem in [[Bryophyte]]s }}

{{term|term= phyllode |content= [[phyllode]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''adj.'' '''phyllodineous'''}} A leaf with the blade much reduced or absent, and in which the petiole and or [[#rachis|rachis]] perform the functions of the whole leaf, e.g. many [[acacia]]s. Compare [[#cladode|cladode]].}}

{{term|term= phyllopodium |content= [[phyllopodium]] }}
{{defn|defn= (in ferns) A short outgrowth of the stem on which the [[#frond|frond]] is borne and which remains attached to the [[#rhizome|rhizome]] after the frond has been shed.}}

{{term|term= phyllosphere |content= [[phyllosphere]] }}
{{defn|defn= The above-ground surface of plants as a habitat for [[#epiphyte|epiphytic]] microorganisms.}}

{{term|term= phytomelan |content= [[phytomelan]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|Also '''phytomelanin'''; ''adj.'' '''phytomelanous'''}} A black, inert, organic material that forms a crust-like covering of some seeds, commonly found in [[Asparagales]], [[Asteraceae]], etc.}}

{{term|term= pilose |content= [[pilose]] }}
{{defn|defn= covered with soft, weak, thin and clearly separated hairs, which are usually defined as long and sometimes ascending.}}

{{term|term= pinna |content= [[Frond#Pinnate fronds|pinna]] }}
{{defn|defn= (plural pinnae) a primary segment of a [[#compound|compound]] leaf.}}

{{term|term= pinnate |content= [[pinnate]] }}
{{defn|defn= a [[#compound|compound]] leaf with [[#leaflets|leaflets]] arranged on each side of a common petiole or [[#axis|axis]]; also applied to how the lateral [[#vein|veins]] are arranged in relation to the main vein.}}

{{term|term= pinnatifid |content= [[pinnatifid]] }}
{{defn|defn= pinnately lobed.}}

{{term|term= pinnatisect |content= [[pinnatisect]] }}
{{defn|defn= pinnately divided almost to midrib but segments still confluent.}}

{{term|term= pinnule |content= [[Pinnate|pinnule]] }}
{{defn|defn= ultimate free division (or [[#leaflets|leaflet]]) of a [[#compound|compound]] leaf, or a pinnate subdivision of a multipinnate leaf.}}

{{term|term= pistil |content= [[pistil]] }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= a single [[#carpel|carpel]] when the carpels are free.}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= a group of carpels when the carpels are united by the fusion of their walls.}}

{{term|term = pistillate flower |content= [[pistillate flower]]}}
{{defn|defn= a flower containing [[#pistil|pistils]] but no [[#stamen|stamens]]}}

{{term|term = pistillode |content= pistillode }}
{{defn|defn=  A sterile or rudimentary pistil. }}

[[File:Tracheid of oak (from Marshall Ward).png|thumb|upright=0.7|right|[[Tracheid]] of oak shows [[#pit|pits]] along the cell walls.]]
{{term|term= pit }}
{{defn|defn= in [[tracheary element]]s, a section of the cell wall where the secondary wall is missing, and the primary wall is present. Pits generally occur in pairs and link two cells.}}

{{term|term= pith |content= [[pith]] }}
{{defn|defn= the central region of a stem, inside the [[#vascular cylinder|vascular cylinder]]; the spongy [[ground tissue|parenchymatous]] central tissue in some stems and roots.}}

{{term|term= placenta |content= [[Placentation|placenta]] }}
{{defn|defn= the tissue within an ovary to which the ovules are attached.}}

{{term|term= placentation |content= [[placentation]] }}
{{defn|defn= the arrangement of ovules inside ovary; for example axile, free-central, parietal, marginal, basal, or apical.}}

[[File:Caloplaca thallincola.jpg|thumb|right|upright=0.7|This [[crustose]] [[lichen]], ''[[Caloplaca thallincola]]'', is placodioid because of the radiating arms in its growth pattern.]]
{{term|term= placodioid |content= [[placodioid]] }}
{{defn|defn= The form of a lichen [[thallus]] which radiates outward with the ends of the radiating arms peeling up from the substrate, but which lack a cortex on the underside (unlike [[#foliose|foliose]] lichens).}}

{{term|term= Plant Breeders Rights |content= [[Plant Breeders Rights]] (PBR) }}
{{defn|defn= these rights, governed by Plant Breeder's Rights Acts give the plant breeder legal protection over the propagation of a cultivar, and the exclusive rights to produce and to sell it, including the right to license others to produce and sell plants and reproductive material of a registered, deliberately bred variety. Cf. UPOV.}}

{{term|term= Plant Variety Rights |content= [[Plant Variety Rights]] (PVR) }}
{{defn|defn= governed by the Plant Variety Rights the registration of new varieties is now governed by Plant Breeders Rights.}}

{{term|term= Plastochron |content= [[Plastochron]] }}
{{defn|defn= the time between successive leaf initiation events.}}

[[File:Whiteflower8.jpg|thumb|right|The [[corolla (flower)|corolla]] of ''[[Datura discolor]]'' is [[#plicate|plicate]].]]
{{term|term= plicate |content= [[pleated|plicate]] }}
{{defn|defn= pleated; folded back and forth longitudinally like a fan, such as the leaves of many palm species. The concept often appears in specific names in forms such as ''[[Kumara plicatilis]]'' and ''[[Acacia plicata]]''. Commonly such names are not correctly appropriate, but are applied to [[Phyllotaxis|distichous]] structures rather than plicate.}}

{{term|term= -[[plinerved]] }}
{{defn|defn= (of leaves) a suffix indicating that the main nerves are lateral and arise from a point distinctly above the base of the leaf. Combined with a numerical prefix to form words like 3-plinerved, 5-plinerved, and so on. Such leaves are especially characteristic of the family Melastomataceae.}}

{{term|term= plumose |content= [[plumose]] }}
{{defn|defn= like a feather; with fine hairs branching from a main axis.}}

{{term|term= plumule |content= [[plumule]] }}
{{defn|defn= the part of an embryo that gives rise to the shoot system of a plant. Compare [[#radicle|radicle]].}}

{{term|term= pluriflor }}
{{defn|defn= having many flowers per [[inflorescence]]. See also [[#pauciflor|pauciflor]] and [[#uniflor|uniflor]].}}

{{term|term= pluriovulate }}
{{defn|defn= having many [[ovules]] as in [[Placentation|placentae]], [[carpels]] or [[Ovary (botany)|ovaries]].}}

{{term|term= pneumatophore |content= [[pneumatophore]] }}
{{defn|defn= a vertical, aerial (at low tide) appendage to the roots of some plants, through which gases are exchanged, e.g. on [[#mangrove|mangroves]].}}

{{term|term= pod }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= a [[#legume|legume]], the fruit of a leguminous plant, a dry fruit of a single [[#carpel|carpel]], splitting along two [[#suture|sutures]].}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= [[#siliqua|siliqua]] and [[#silicula|silicula]], the fruit of [[Brassicaceae]], a dry fruit composed of two [[#carpel|carpels]] separated by a partition.}}

{{term|term= pollen |content= [[pollen]] }}
{{defn|defn= powdery mass shed from anthers (of angiosperms) or microsporangia (of gymnosperms); the microspores of seed plants; pollen-grains.}}

{{term|term= pollen-mass |content= [[pollen-mass]] }}
{{defn|defn= pollen-grains cohering by a waxy texture or fine threads into a single body; [[#pollinium|pollinium]], e.g. in [[Orchidaceae|orchids]].}}

{{term|term= pollen transmitting tissue }}
{{defn|defn= the tissue in the [[style (botany)|style]] of a flower through which the [[pollen tube]]s grow.}}

{{term|term= pollination |content= [[pollination]] }}
{{defn|defn= the transfer of pollen from the male organ ([[#anther|anther]]) to the receptive region of a female organ ([[#stigma|stigma]]).}}

{{term|term= pollinium |content= [[pollinium]] }}
{{defn|defn= see [[#pollen-mass|pollen-mass]].}}

{{term|term= polygamodioecious |content= [[polygamodioecious]] }}
{{defn|defn= having bisexual and male flowers on some plants and bisexual and female flowers on others. Compare [[#androdioecious|androdioecious]], [[#andromonoecious|andromonoecious]], [[#dioecious|dioecious]], [[#monoecious|monoecious]], [[#polygamomonoecious|polygamomonoecious]], [[#polygamous|polygamous]].}}

{{term|term= polygamomonoecious |content= [[polygamomonoecious]] }}
{{defn|defn= having male, female and bisexual flowers on the same plant. Compare [[#androdioecious|androdioecious]], [[#andromonoecious|andromonoecious]], [[#polygamodioecious|polygamodioecious]], [[#polygamous|polygamous]]. }}

{{term|term= polygamous |content= [[polygamous]] }}
{{defn|defn= having [[#bisexual|bisexual]] and [[#unisexual|unisexual]] flowers on the same plant.}}

{{term|term= polymorphic |content= [[wikt:polymorphic|polymorphic]] }}
{{defn|defn= of several different kinds (in respect to shape and/or size), hence [[Polymorphism (biology)|polymorphism]]. See also '''[[#monomorphic|monomorphic]]''' (a single type) and '''[[#dimorphic|dimorphic]]''' (two types)}}

{{term|term= polyploid |content= [[polyploid]] }}
{{defn|defn= with more than two of the basic sets of [[chromosomes]] in the [[cell nucleus|nucleus]]; any [[sporophyte]] with cells containing three or more complete sets of chromosomes.  Various combinations of words or numbers with '-ploid' indicate the number of [[#haploid|haploid]] sets of chromosomes, e.g. triploid = 3 sets, [[#tetraploid|tetraploid]] = 4 sets, pentaploid = 5 sets, hexaploid = 6 sets, and so on.}}

{{term|term= polystemonous |content= polystemonous }}
{{defn|defn= having [[#numerous|numerous]] [[#stamens|stamens]]; the number of stamens being at least twice the number of sepals or petals, but not strictly three or four times that number.}}

{{term|term= pome |content= [[pome]] }}
{{defn|defn= a fruit that has developed partly from the ovary wall but mostly from the [[hypanthium]], e.g. [[apple]].}}

{{term|term= population |content= [[population]] }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= all individuals of one or more species within a prescribed area.}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= a group of organisms of one species, occupying a defined area and usually isolated to some degree from other similar groups.}}
{{defn|no=3|defn= in statistics, the whole group of items or individuals under investigation.}}

{{term|term= poricidal |content= [[poricidal]] }}
{{defn|defn= opening by pores, like the [[Capsule (fruit)|capsule]] of a poppy, or like the anthers in several families of plants. compare: [[#longicidal|longicidal]]}}

{{term|term= posterior |content= [[Posterior (anatomy)|posterior]] }}
{{defn|defn= positioned behind, towards the rear, [[#proximal|proximal]]. Compare [[#anterior|anterior]], [[#distal|distal]].}}

{{term|term= prickle |content= [[prickle (botany)|prickle]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''adj.'' '''prickly'''}} A hard, pointed outgrowth from the surface of a plant (involving several layers of cells but not containing a [[#vein|vein]]); a sharp outgrowth from the bark, detachable without tearing wood. Compare [[#thorn|thorn]].}}

{{term|term= primary species |content= [[primary species]] }}
{{defn|defn= In [[lichens]], a species reproducing mainly by [[sexual reproduction]], not [[vegetative reproduction]].}}

{{term|term= primary vein |content= primary vein }}
{{defn|defn= The single [[#vein|vein]] or array of veins that is conspicuously larger than any others in a leaf. In [[#pinnate|pinnate]] [[#venation|venation]], the single primary vein can generally be found in the middle of the leaf; in [[#palmate|palmate]] venation, several such veins radiate from a point at or near the base of the leaf.}}

{{term|term= propagule |content= [[propagule]] }}
{{defn|defn= In [[lichen]]s, a part of the [[#thallus|thallus]] that has both fungal and algal parts and can break off for [[vegetative reproduction]], e.g. an [[#isidium|isidium]], [[#phyllidium|phyllidium]], [[#phyllocladium|phyllocladium]], or [[#soredium|soredium]]).}}

{{term|term= prophyll |content= [[prophyll]] }}
{{defn|defn= A leaf formed at the base of a [[#shoot|shoot]], usually smaller than those formed later.}}

{{term|term= pro parte |content= [[pro parte]] }}
{{defn|defn= In part; in nomenclature, used to denote that the preceding taxon includes more than one currently recognized entity, and that only one of those entities is being considered.}}

{{term|term= procumbent |content= [[procumbent]] }}
{{defn|defn= Spreading along the ground but not rooting at the [[#node|nodes]]; not as close to the ground as [[#prostrate|prostrate]].}}

{{term|term= propagule |content= [[propagule]] }}
{{defn|defn= Any structure capable of generating a new plant; includes [[#seed|seeds]], [[#spore|spores]], [[#bulbils|bulbils]], etc.}}

{{term|term= prostrate }}
{{defn|defn= Lying flat on the ground.}}

{{term|term= protandrous |content= [[protandrous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having male sex organs which mature before the female ones, e.g. a flower shedding pollen before the stigma is receptive. Compare [[#protogynous|protogynous]].}}

{{term|term= proteranthous |content= [[proteranthous]] }}
{{defn|defn= new leaves appear before flowers. See also '''[[#hysteranthous|hysteranthous]]''' and '''[[#synanthous|synanthous]]'''}}

{{term|term= prothallus |content= [[prothallus]] }}
{{defn|defn= A [[#gametophyte]] plant, usually flattened and delicate, e.g. in ferns and fern allies.}}

{{term|term= protogynous |content= [[protogynous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having female sex organs which mature before the male ones, e.g. a flower shedding [[#pollen|pollen]] after the [[#stigma|stigma]] has ceased to be receptive. Compare [[#protandrous|protandrous]].}}

{{term|term= proximal |content= [[Proximo distal|proximal]] }}
{{defn|defn= Near the point of origin or attachment. Compare [[#distal|distal]].}}

{{term|term= pruinose |content= [[pruinose]] }}
{{defn|defn= Covered with a powdery, waxy material; having a [[#bloom|bloom]].}}

{{term|term= pseudanthium |content= [[pseudanthium]] }}
{{defn|defn= A type of [[#inflorescence|inflorescence]] occurring in the [[Asteraceae]] and [[Euphorbiaceae]], in which multiple flowers are grouped together to form a flower-like structure, commonly called a [[pseudanthium|head]] or [[#capitulum|capitulum]].}}

{{term|term= pseudo- |content= [[pseudo]]- }}
{{defn|defn= A prefix meaning "false, not genuine", e.g. a pseudo-bulb is a thickened, bulb-like internode in [[Orchidaceae|orchids]], but not an actual [[#bulb|bulb]].}}

{{term|term= pseudostipule |content= [[pseudostipule]] }}
{{defn|defn= An enlarged, persistent [[#axillary bud|axillary bud]] scale that resembles a [[#stipule|stipule]]; common in [[Bignoniaceae]].}}

{{term|term= pseudoverticillate |content= [[pseudoverticillate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having the appearance of being whorled ([[#verticillate|verticillate]]), without actually being so.}}

{{term|term= puberulous |content= [[:wikt:puberulous|puberulous]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|Also '''puberulent'''.}} Covered with minute soft erect hairs.}}

{{term|term= pubescent |content= [[Pubescent (botany)|pubescent]] }}
{{defn|defn= Downy; covered with short, soft, erect hairs.}}

{{term|term= pulverulent |content= pulverulent }}
{{defn|defn= Having powdery or crumbly particles as if pulverized.}}

{{term|term= pulvinate |content= pulvinate }}
{{defn|defn= Having a [[#pulvinus|pulvinus]].}}

{{term|term= pulvinus |content= [[pulvinus]] }}
{{defn|defn= a swelling at either end of a [[#petiole|petiole]] of a leaf or [[#petiolule|petiolule]] of a leaflet, e.g. in [[Fabaceae]], that permits leaf movement. }}

{{term|term= punctate |content= punctate }}
{{defn|defn= marked with dots.}}

{{term|term= punctiform |content= punctiform }}
{{defn|defn= Dot-like.}}

{{term|term= pungent }}
{{defn|defn= Having a sharp, hard point.}}

{{term|term= pustule |content= [[pustule]] }}
{{defn|defn= A blister-like swelling.}}

{{term|term= pustulate |content= [[pustulate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having [[#pustule|pustule]]s.}}

{{term|term= pyramidal |content= [[pyramidal]] }}
{{defn|defn= (of a growth habit) Tetrahedral; pyramid-shaped.}}

{{term|term= pyrene |content= [[pyrena|pyrene]] }}
{{defn|defn= The stone of a [[#drupe|drupe]], consisting of the seed surrounded by the hardened [[#endocarp|endocarp]].}}

{{term|term= pyriform }}
{{defn|defn= [[Pear]]-shaped; a term for solid shapes that are broadest in the upper third and abruptly narrowed near the base.}}

