==R==
{{glossary}}

{{term|term= raceme |content= [[raceme]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''adj.'' '''racemose'''}} An [[#indeterminate|indeterminate]] [[#inflorescence|inflorescence]] in which the main axis produces a series of flowers on lateral stalks, the oldest at the base and the youngest at the top. Compare [[#spike|spike]].}}

{{term|term= rachilla |content= [[rachilla]] (rhachilla) }}
{{defn|defn= the axis of a grass [[#spikelet|spikelet]], above the [[#glumes|glumes]].}}

{{term|term= rachis |content= [[rachis]] }}
{{defn|defn= (plural rachises; rachides) the axis of an inflorescence or a [[#pinnate|pinnate]] leaf; for example ferns; secondary [[#rachis|rachis]] is the axis of a [[#pinna|pinna]] in a bipinnate leaf distal to and including the lowermost [[#pedicel|pedicel]] attachment.}}

{{term|term= radial }}
{{defn|defn= with structures radiating from a central point as [[spoke]]s on a wheel, for example, the lateral spines of a cactus.}}

{{term|term= radiate }}
{{defn|defn= of daisies, of a capitulum, with [[#ray|ray]] [[#floret|florets]] surrounding disc florets.}}

{{term|term= radical |content= [[radical (botany)|radical]] }}
{{defn|defn= springing from the root; clustered at base of stem.}}

{{term|term= radicle |content= [[radicle]] }}
{{defn|defn= the part of an [[#embryo|embryo]] giving rise to the root system of a plant. Compare [[#plumule|plumule]].}}

{{term|term= rainforest |content= [[rainforest]] }}
{{defn|defn= a moist temperate or tropical forest dominated by broad-leaved trees that form a continuous canopy. }}

{{term|term= ramet |content= [[ramet]] }}
{{defn|defn= an individual member of a [[#clone|clone]].}}

{{term|term= ramicaul |content= [[ramicaul]] }}
{{defn|defn= a single-leafed stem, as in [[Pleurothallis]] orchids.<ref name="BotVocab">{{cite book |author1=Pell, Susan K. |author2=Angell, Bobbi |title=A Botanist's Vocabulary: 1300 Terms Explained and Illustrated |publisher=Timber Press |location=Portland, OR |year=2016 |pages=169 |isbn=978-1-604-69563-2 |oclc= |doi= }}</ref> }}

{{term|term= ray }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= zygomorphic (ligulate) [[#flower|flowers]] in a [[#radiate|radiate]] flowerhead, that is, ray-florets/flowers, for example [[Asteraceae]].}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= each of the branches of an [[#umbel|umbel]].}}

{{term|term= receptacle |content= [[receptacle (botany)|receptacle]] }}
{{defn|defn= the [[#axis|axis]] of a [[#flower|flower]], in other words, [[floral axis]]; [[#torus|torus]]; for example in [[Asteraceae]], the floral base or [[#receptacle|receptacle]] is the expanded tip of the peduncle on which the flowers are [[#inserted|inserted]].}}

{{term|term= recurved |content= [[recurved]] }}
{{defn|defn= bent or curved backwards or downwards.}}

{{term|term= reduplicate }}
{{defn|defn= folded outwards, or with the two [[#abaxial|abaxial]] surfaces together.}}

{{term|term= reflexed |content=[[:wikt:reflexed|reflexed]] }}
{{defn|defn= bent sharply back or down.}}

{{term|term= registered name }}
{{defn|defn= a [[cultivar]] name accepted by the relevant [[International Cultivar Registration Authority]].}}

{{term|term= registration }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= the act of recording a new [[cultivar]] name with an [[International Cultivar Registration Authority]].}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= recording a new cultivar name with a statutory authority like the [[Plant Breeder’s Rights Office]].}}
{{defn|no=3|defn= recording a [[trademark]] with a trade marks office.}}

{{term|term= regular }}
{{defn|defn= See [[#actinomorphic|actinomorphic]].}}

{{term|term= reniform |content= [[reniform]] }}
{{defn|defn= Kidney-shaped.}}

{{term|term= resupinate |content= [[resupinate]]}}
{{defn|no=1|defn= In [[botany]], describing leaves or flowers that are in an inverted position because the [[Petiole (botany)|petiole]] or [[Pedicel (botany)|pedicel]], respectively, is twisted 180 degrees. compare: [[#hyper-resupinate]]}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= In [[lichenology]], referring to either having or being a fruiting body that lies flat on the [[substrate (biology)|substrate]], with the [[hymenium]] either over the whole surface or at the periphery.}}

{{term|term= reticulate |}}
{{defn|defn= forming a network (or reticulum), e.g. [[#vein|veins]] that join one another at more than one point.}}

{{term|term= retrorse |content= retrorse }}
{{defn|defn= Bent backwards or downwards. Compare [[#antrorse|antrorse]].}}

{{term|term= retuse |content= [[retuse]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having a blunt ([[#obtuse|obtuse]]) and slightly notched apex.}}

{{term|term= revision }}
{{defn|defn= an account of a particular plant group, like an abbreviated or simplified [[#monograph|monograph]].  Sometimes confined to the plants of a particular region.  Similar to a monograph in clearly distinguishing the taxa and providing a means for their identification. Compare [[#monograph|monograph]].}}

{{term|term= revolute }}
{{defn|defn= rolled under (downwards or backwards), for example when the edges of leaves are rolled under towards the midrib. Compare [[#involute|involute]].}}

{{term|term= rhachis }}
{{defn|defn= see [[#rachis|rachis]].}}

{{term|term= rhizine |content= [[rhizine]] }}
{{defn|defn= The "root" or "trunk" projection of a [[foliose]] [[lichen]] that attaches the lichen to the [[Substrate (biology)|substrate]] (what the lichen is growing on)}}

{{term|term= rhizodermis |content= [[rhizodermis]] }}
{{defn|defn= the root [[Epidermis (botany)|epidermis]], the outermost primary cell layer of the root}}

{{term|term= rhizome |content= [[rhizome]] }}
{{defn|defn= a perennial underground stem usually growing horizontally.  See also [[#stolon|stolon]]. Abbreviation: rhiz.}}

{{term|term= rhizosphere |content= [[rhizosphere]] }}
{{defn|defn= the below-ground surface of plants and adjacent soil as a habitat for microorganisms. }}

{{term|term= rhombic }}
{{defn|defn= like a [[rhombus]]: an oblique figure with four equal sides. Compare [[#trapeziform|trapeziform]], [[#trullate|trullate]].}}

{{term|term= rhomboid |content= [[rhomboid]] }}
{{defn|defn= a four-sided figure with opposite sides parallel but with adjacent sides an unequal length (like an oblique rectangle); see also [[#rhombic|rhombic]].}}

{{term|term= rhomboidal |content= [[rhomboidal]] }}
{{defn|defn= a shape, for instance of a leaf, that is roughly diamond-shaped with length equal to width.}}

{{term|term= rimose |content= [[rimose]] }}
{{defn|defn= with many cracks, as in the surface of a [[lichen|crustose areolate lichen]].}}

{{term|term= root |content= [[root]] }}
{{defn|defn= a unit of a plant's axial system which is usually underground, does not bear leaves, tends to grow downwards, and is typically derived from the [[#radicle|radicle]] of the [[#embryo|embryo]].}}

{{term|term= root hairs |content= [[root hairs]] }}
{{defn|defn= outgrowths of the outermost layer of cells just behind the root tips, functioning as water-absorbing organs.}}

{{term|term= root microbiome |content= [[root microbiome]] }}
{{defn|defn= the dynamic community of microorganisms associated with plant roots.}}

{{term|term= rootstock |content= [[rootstock]] }}
{{defn|defn= 1. the part of a budded or [[grafting|grafted]] plant which supplies the root system, also simply called a [[#stock|stock]]. }}
{{defn|no=2|defn= plants selected to produce a root system with some specific attribute, e.g. a virus-free rootstock. }}

{{term|term= rosette |content= [[Rosette (botany)|rosette]] }}
{{defn|defn= when parts are not whorled or opposite but appear so, due to the contractions of [[#internode|internodes]], e.g. the petals in a double rose or a basal cluster of leaves (usually close to the ground) in some plants.}}

{{term|term= rostrate |content= [[rostrum (anatomy)|rostrate]] }}
{{defn|defn= with a beak.}}

{{term|term= rotate }}
{{defn|defn= circular and flattened; for example a [[#corolla|corolla]] with a very short tube and spreading lobes (for instance some [[Solanaceae]]).}}

{{term|term= ruderal |content= [[Ruderal species|ruderal]] }}
{{defn|defn= a plant that colonises or occupies disturbed waste ground. See also [[#weed|weed]].}}

[[File:Nsr-slika-431.png|thumb|right|The [[#runcinate|runcinate]] lobes of a ''[[Taraxacum officinale]]'' leaf point downwards]]
{{term|term= rudimentary }}
{{defn|defn= poorly developed and not functional. Compare [[#vestigal|vestigial]].}}

{{term|term= rugose }}
{{defn|defn= Wrinkled.}}

{{term|term= rugulose |content= rugulose }}
{{defn|defn= Finely wrinkled.}}

{{term|term= ruminate |content= [[endosperm|ruminate]] }}
{{defn|defn= (usually applied to [[#endosperm|endosperm]]) Irregularly grooved or ridged; appearing chewed, e.g. the endosperm in certain members of [[Myristicaceae]].}}

{{term|term= runcinate |content= runcinate }}
{{defn|defn= Sharply [[#pinnatifid|pinnatifid]] or cleft, with the segments directed downward.}}

{{term|term= runner }}
{{defn|defn= See [[#stolon|stolon]].}}

{{term|term= rupicolous |content= [[wikt:rupicolous|rupicolous]] }}
{{defn|defn= [[#rupestral|Rupestral]], [[#saxicolous|saxicolous]], growing on or among rocks. Compare [[#epilithic|epilithic]] and [[lithophytic]].}}

{{term|term= rush }}
{{defn|defn= A plant belonging to the family [[Juncaceae]] or, more loosely, applied to various [[#monocotyledon|monocotyledons]].}}

