{{defn|defn= Slightly leathery or [[#coriaceous|coriaceous]].}}

{{term|term= subgenus |content= [[subgenus]] }}
{{defn|defn= A category of supplementary taxa intermediate between [[#genus|genus]] and [[#section|section]]. The name of a subgenus is a singular noun, always has a capital initial letter and is used in combination with the generic name, e.g. ''[[Primula]]'' subgenus ''Primula''.}}

{{term|term= subglobose| content=[[:wikt:subglobose|subglobose]] }}
{{defn|defn= Inflated, but less than spherical. See also [[#globose|globose]].}}

{{term|term= subshrub |content= [[subshrub]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|Also called an '''[[#undershrub|undershrub]]'''.}} A small [[#shrub|shrub]] which may have partially [[#herbaceous|herbaceous]] stems, but generally a woody plant less than {{convert|1|m|ft}} high.}}

{{term|term= subspecies |content= [[subspecies]] }}
{{defn|defn= A taxonomic category within a [[#species|species]], usually used for geographically isolated or morphologically distinct populations of the same species. Its taxonomic rank occurs between species and [[#variety|variety]].}}

{{term|term= subtend |content= [[subtend]] }}
{{defn|defn= To stand beneath or close to, as in a [[#bract|bract]] at the base of a flower.}}

{{term|term= subquadrangular |content= subquadrangular }}
{{defn|defn= Not quite square. Compare [[wikt:quadrangular|quadrangular]].}}

{{term|term= subulate |content= [[subulate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Narrow and tapering gradually to a fine point.}}

{{term|term= succulent |content= [[succulent]] }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= Juicy or fleshy.}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= A plant with a fleshy habit.}}

{{term|term= sucker |content= [[Basal shoot|sucker]] }}
{{defn|defn= A [[#shoot|shoot]] of more or less subterranean origin; an [[#erect|erect]] shoot originating from a bud on a root or a [[#rhizome|rhizome]], sometimes at some distance from the stem of the plant.}}

{{term|term= suffrutex |content= [[suffrutex]] }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|''pl.'' suffrutices}} A [[#subshrub|subshrub]] or undershrub.}}

{{term|term= sulcate |content= [[:wikt:sulcate|sulcate]] }}
{{defn|defn= Furrowed; grooved. May be single (''monosulcate''), two (''bisulcate'') or many (''polysulcate'').}}

{{term|term= superficial }}
{{defn|defn= On the surface.}}

{{term|term= superior }}
{{defn|defn= Of an [[#ovary|ovary]], borne above the level of attachment of the other floral parts, or above the base of a [[#hypanthium|hypanthium]]. Compare [[#inferior|inferior]] and [[#half-inferior|half-inferior]].}}

{{term|term= suspended }}
{{defn|defn= Of an [[#ovule|ovule]], when attached slightly below the summit of the ovary. Compare [[#pendulous|pendulous]].}}

{{term|term= suture |content= [[suture (anatomy)|suture]] }}
{{defn|defn= A junction or seam of union. See [[#fissure|fissure]] and [[#commissure|commissure]].}}

{{term|term= sward }}
{{defn|defn= Extensive, more or less even cover of a surface, e.g. a lawn grass. Compare [[#tussock|tussock]].}}

{{term|term= sympatric |content= [[sympatric]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having more or less similar or overlapping ranges of distribution.}}

{{term|term= sympodial }}
{{defn|defn= A mode of growth in which the main axis is repeatedly terminated and replaced with a lateral branch. Examples occur in the family [[Combretaceae]], including the genera ''[[Terminalia]]'' and ''[[Combretum]]''.}}

{{term|term= syconium |content= [[syconium]] }}
{{defn|defn= A hollow [[infructescence]] containing [[multiple fruit]], such as that of a [[Common fig|fig]].}}

{{term|term= syn- |content= syn- {{anchor|syn|syn-|sym|sym-}} }}
{{defn|defn= {{ghat|Also '''sym-'''.}} A prefix meaning "with, together".}}

{{term|term= symmetrical |content= [[symmetry (geometry)|symmetrical]] }}
{{defn|defn= Capable of being divided into at least two equal, mirror-image halves (e.g. [[#zygomorphic|zygomorphic]]) or having rotational symmetry (e.g. [[#regular|regular]] or [[#actinomorphic|actinomorphic]]). Compare [[#irregular|irregular]] and [[#asymmetrical|asymmetrical]].}}

{{term|term= sympetalous |content= [[sympetalous]] }}
{{defn|defn= Having united ([[#connate|connate]] or fused) [[#petal|petals]]. See also [[#syntepalous|syntepalous]] (having fused [[#tepal|tepals]]).}}

{{term|term= synangium |content= [[synangium]] }}
{{defn|defn= A fused aggregate of [[#sporangia|sporangia]], e.g. in the trilocular sporangia of the whisk fern ''[[Psilotum]]''.}}

{{term|term= synanthous |content= synanthous }}
{{defn|defn= A type of growth in which new leaves and flowers appear and die back at the same time. See also [[#hysteranthous|hysteranthous]] and [[#proteranthous|proteranthous]].}}

{{term|term= synaptospermy |content= [[synaptospermy]] }}
{{defn|defn= The dispersal of [[diaspore (botany)|diaspores]] as units, where each bears more than one seed, for example where each diaspore comprises an entire inflorescence, as in ''[[Brunsvigia]]'' or multi-seeded fruit as in ''[[Tribulus]]'' zeyheri. ''Ephemeral'' synaptospermy is the term for when the diaspores split into units containing fewer or single seeds each, as in most [[tumbleweed]]s. ''True'' synaptospermy is when the diaspore generally remains entire until germination, as commonly happens in species of ''[[Grielum]]''.}}

{{term|term= syncarpous |content= [[syncarpous]] }}
{{defn|defn= (of a [[#gynoecium|gynoecium]]) Composed of united [[#carpel|carpels]].}}

{{term|term= synonym |content= [[synonym (taxonomy)|synonym]] }}
{{defn|defn= An outdated or 'alternative' name for the same taxon.}}

{{term|term= synoecious |content= [[synoecious]] }}
{{defn|defn= A synonym of [[#bisexual|bisexual]].}}

{{term|term= syntepalous|content= syntepalous}}
{{defn|defn= Having fused [[#tepal|tepals]]. See also [[#symppetalous|sympetalous]] (having fused [[#petal|petals]]).}}

{{glossary end}}

