{{term|term= umbel |content= [[umbel]] }}
{{defn|defn= A [[#raceme|racemose]] inflorescence in which all the individual flower stalks arise in a cluster at the top of the [[#peduncle|peduncle]] and are of about equal length; in a simple umbel, each stalk is unbranched and bears only one flower. A [[#cyme|cymose]] umbel looks similar to an ordinary umbel but its flowers open centrifugally.}}

