==W==

{{glossary}}
[[File:Watershoots.JPG|thumb|'''Watershoots''']]
{{term|term= warty |content= [[warty]] }}
{{defn|defn= A surface covered with small round protuberances, especially in fruit, leaves, twigs and bark. See [[#tuberculate|tuberculate]].}}

{{term|term= watershoot |content= [[watershoot]] }}
{{defn|defn= An erect, strong-growing or [[#epicormic|epicormic]] shoot developing from near the base of a shrub or tree, but distinct from a [[#sucker|sucker]].}}

{{term|term= weed |content= [[weed]] }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= Any plant growing where it is not wanted; commonly associated with disrupted habitats. See also [[#ruderal|ruderal]].}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= (agricultural weed) An unwanted plant which grows among agricultural [[#crop|crops]].}}
{{defn|no=3|defn= (environmental weed) A naturalised, exotic or ecologically 'out-of-balance' indigenous species outside the agricultural or garden context which, as a result of invasion, adversely affects the survival or regeneration of indigenous species in natural or partly natural vegetation communities.<ref>Carr, G.W., in Foreman & Walsh, 1993.</ref>}}

{{term|term= wild }}
{{defn|defn= Originating from a known wild or purely natural habitat ([[wilderness]]).}}

{{term|term= whorl |content= [[Whorl (botany)|whorl]] }}
{{defn|defn= A ring of organs borne at the same level on an [[#axis|axis]], for example leaves, [[#bract|bracts]] or floral parts.}}

{{term|term= wing }}
{{defn|no=1|defn= A membranous expansion of a fruit or seed which aids in dispersal, for instance on [[pine]] seeds.}}
{{defn|no=2|defn= A thin flange of tissue extending beyond the normal outline of a structure, e.g. on the column of some [[orchid]]s, on stems, on petioles.}}
{{defn|no=3|defn= One of the two lateral petals of a flower of subfamily [[Faboideae]] of family [[Fabaceae]], located between the [[#adaxial|adaxial]] standard (banner) petal and the two [[#abaxial|abaxial]] keel petals.}}

{{term|term= woolly |content= [[woolly]] }}
{{defn|defn= Very densely covered with long, more or less matted or intertwined hairs, resembling a sheep's [[wool]].}}

